<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Crossings">Crossings</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Connecticut_River&amp;action=edit&amp;section=24" title="Edit section: Crossings">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<div class="rellink relarticle mainarticle">Main article: <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_crossings_of_the_Connecticut_River" title="List of crossings of the Connecticut River">List of crossings of the Connecticut River</a></div>
<p>The Connecticut River is a barrier to travel between western and eastern New England. Several major transportation corridors cross the river including <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amtrak" title="Amtrak">Amtrak</a>'s <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Northeast_Corridor" title="Northeast Corridor">Northeast Corridor</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interstate_95_in_Connecticut" title="Interstate 95 in Connecticut">Interstate 95</a> (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Connecticut_Turnpike" title="Connecticut Turnpike">Connecticut Turnpike</a>), <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interstate_90" title="Interstate 90">Interstate 90</a> (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Massachusetts_Turnpike" title="Massachusetts Turnpike">Massachusetts Turnpike</a>), <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interstate_89" title="Interstate 89">Interstate 89</a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interstate_93" title="Interstate 93">Interstate 93</a>, and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interstate_84_(east)" title="Interstate 84 (east)" class="mw-redirect">Interstate 84</a>. In addition, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interstate_91" title="Interstate 91">Interstate 91</a>, whose route largely follows the river north-south, crosses it twice - once in Connecticut and once in Massachusetts.</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Sites_of_interest">Sites of interest</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Connecticut_River&amp;action=edit&amp;section=25" title="Edit section: Sites of interest">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Connecticut_River_Museum" title="Connecticut River Museum">Connecticut River Museum</a> in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Essex,_Connecticut" title="Essex, Connecticut">Essex, Connecticut</a></li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Quadrangle" title="The Quadrangle">Connecticut Valley Historical Museum</a> in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Springfield,_Massachusetts" title="Springfield, Massachusetts">Springfield, Massachusetts</a></li>
</ul>
